Fine Cooking - August/September 2017 - True PDF - zeke23
English | True PDF | 104 pages | 94 MB


Fine Cooking is a magazine that is devoted to the creation of high quality dishes and desserts. Featured in the magazine are countless recipes, as well as informative how-to guides for various cooking and baking techniques.

Fine Cooking is known well for publishing countless recipes for readers to follow. The recipes found in the magazine, such as one for Grilled Steak and Watercress Sandwiches, are genuinely meant to impress. Seasonal recipes are also included in Fine Cooking. One recent issue includes both Autumn Apple Desserts and various fall soups. Also included are drink and dessert recipes that can be paired perfectly with the main recipes in the magazine.

Readers of Fine Cooking are treated to how-to guides for various cooking and baking techniques with each issue. These guides cover anything from cooking rice and boiling eggs, relatively simple things, to butterflying a chicken and grilling fish steaks. One recently published guide teaches readers to roll out perfect pie crusts, something that many experts still often struggle with.

A subscription to Fine Cooking makes a great gift for anyone who loves to cook and would be interested in learning about new recipes and techniques. On our website, you can either order a new subscription for yourself or as a gift, or you can easily renew a subscription to Fine Cooking
